                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d726">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00/8612: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-11-24T12:00:00-06:00"
                            >November 24, 1936—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 2:27 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>233. Committees representing conservative and liberal supporters of biparty
                    agreement met yesterday and decided to abstain from voting on December 8th thus
                    virtually withdrawing Argüello-Espinosa ticket and leaving Somoza as sole
                    Presidential candidate.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Ray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
